  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Unger et al. (2024) proposed a Transformer-based deep learning architecture, called RETINA, to predict a user's product preference from raw eye-movement data.",
    "They employ a multi-layer bidirectional Transformer architecture, similar to that of Vaswani et al. (2017), to capture intricate temporal relationships between gaze points and predict AOIs by leveraging the Transformer's inherent ability to process long sequential data in parallel.",
    "The evaluation metric depends a lot on the dataset at hand and the type of problem.",
    "We found that accuracy was the predominant ML model evaluation metric, followed by AUC score and F1 score, respectively.",
    "There are various publications that focus on the benefits and limitations of each evaluation metric; for example, accuracy is not suitable for imbalanced data, and F1 score is not suitable when you care equally about the positive and negative classes."
  ],
